Parents, please if you have not been in contact with your child's teacher via class Dojo please call the school today. Our distant learning will begin on Monday and we need to make sure every STAR Coyote student is able to access the lessons and interact with their teacher from home. We will have a soft start next week so that you and your children can learn how connect with us, create a schedule for your home and give us feedback so we can continue to improve. This is uncharted territory for GGPA but together we will create a quality system because that's the Coyote WAY! Havvvvvvvvve a great day!

Principal Crawford

post_text:
Important Notice for GGPA Community March 13, 2020 ‚Äì 6:30PM

After careful consideration George Gervin Prep Academy will be closed to students until further notice beginning March 16, 2020 in order to help contain the spread of COVID-19 in our community. During this time, our school leadership will continue to stay updated on the COVID situation in our county, state and nation.

We want to assure all families and staff that this decision was made only after thoughtful consideration of the facts and the potential impact on our community. We will continue to communicate and provide updates regarding alternative and digital learning for students and timeframe of reopening the school.

Again, GGPA students will not return from Spring Break next week. We will continue to post updates on our web page, our telephone Smart Call system, Facebook and Class Dojo.

Thank you for your patience.

Sincerely,
Principal Crawford
Superintendent Hawkins

It has been another successful year at George Gervin Prep Academy, we appreciate all the help and support from our parents and students. Thank you!

post_text:
Happy New Year from the GGPA family to yours! We are so excited to be entering a brand new year with you. When returning from break, it will be important for us to Start Strong & Stay Strong. We will be in the home stretch of a spectacular school year!

Over the next few days you can help by having your child read with you at home. "According to the National Center for Education Statistics (NCES), a divison of the U.S. Department of Education, children who are read to at home enjoy a substantial advantage over children who are not."

So cuddle up with a great book and spend some quality time together. We can't wait to hear about what you and your child have read.

Again, Happy New Year and we will see you soon!

REMEMBER AZ MERIT TESTING

During each day of testing, students will begin to test first thing in the morning. They will have a morning and an afternoon session. It is very important that students be here, and on time, for the entire school day. If a child begins testing but is then signed out from school, the unfinished portion of the test cannot be scored nor made up. If appointments must be scheduled, we ask that appointments be made after the school day ends.
